Professor Czeisler advised students to set an alarm clock for when they need to go to bed, as well as when they need to wake up, and to be aware of the harmful effects of the "blue light" emitted by electronic screens and LED lights, which can tilt the circadian rhythm, leading to problems falling asleep.
