The Global Citizen Festival, which began in 2012, is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international advocacy group that hopes to eradicate poverty by increasing the number of people actively fighting it.
To receive a free ticket to the event (unless they were willing to pay for a VIP ticket), the concert audience had to complete a series of tasks, or “actions” such as volunteering, sending emails to a world leader, making a phone call, or any other meaningful way that would help raise awareness about their goal of eradicating poverty.
