Since 2011, Global Citizen claims to have recorded more than 19 million “actions” of its supporters, working for a variety of different purposes.
These actions have helped to urge world leaders to announce commitments and policies worth more than $37 billion, intended to affect the lives of more than 2.25 billion people by 2030.
