2004: A massive earthquake on the west coast of Aceh province north of Sumatra caused a tsunami that struck 14 countries along the Indian Ocean coast, killing 226,000 people, more than half of them from Aceh.
2005: A series of strong earthquakes hit the west coast of Sumatra between late March and early April.
